Explanation:
According to the documents, the champions in singles female at the German Open Championships were different people. In one document (file_path: /Users/stefanomarchesin/Research/fshami/Rag/docs/dbpedia_6558/re-ranker-msmarco/55.txt), it is stated that "In August she beat Judy Tegart in straight sets in the final of the singles event at the German Championships in Hamburg and also won the doubles and mixed doubles events." However, there is no information about Annette Van Zyl being a champion at this tournament.

llama3.1.reason: The champion in single female at the 1968 German Open Championships was actually Judy Tegart, not Annette Van Zyl.
